Package: LINGUINE
Title: LINkage GroUps INfErence for Ancestral Genomes
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Carlos", "Vargas-Chávez", email = "carlos.vargas@ibe.upf-csic.es", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Rosa", "Fernández", role = "aut")
  )
Description: A phylogeny-aware pipeline for robust ancestral linkage group (ALG) reconstruction. 
    LINGUINE is specifically designed to handle clades characterized by rapid genome evolution, 
    extensive chromosomal rearrangements, and whole-genome duplications (WGDs). By utilizing 
    full orthogroups rather than restricting to single-copy genes, employing a Hidden Markov Model 
    (HMM) framework to delineate syntenic blocks, and utilizing an iterative post-order traversal 
    of the species tree, LINGUINE resolves complex paralogy and prevents the systematic inflation 
    of inferred ALG counts.
